          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χρώς</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χρωτός</span> and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χροός</span>, dat.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χροΐ</span>, acc. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χρῶτα</span> and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χρόα</span>: properly
          surface, esp. of the body, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">skin, body</span> with reference to
          the skin; then <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">color, complexion</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τρέπεται</span>, ‘changes,’ of turning pale with fear, <i><span class="en">Il. 13.279</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od.
